 Port Elizabeth - The Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service on Friday said that its forecast for the weekend is still on track. "Cold windy conditions will prevail over most of the Eastern Cape on Friday," described Garth Sampson, Client Liaison Officer for the SA Weather Service in the Eastern Cape. "Rainy conditions will persist until later on Saturday. "Light snowfalls are expected on over the peaks of the Cape Fold Mountains and the Winterberg in the areas of Beaufort West through Graaf Reinett to Stutterheim." Sampson said that snow is also possible over the southern Drakensberg. "Very cold conditions will prevail until Sunday morning," he added. "Temperatures will start recovering from Sunday afternoon." Station Names 19 Nelson Mandela Bay  AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 4.6 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 4.4 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 4.4 AWSH Chatty NIL AWS Coega NIL AWSH Fettes Road 0.6 ARS Flower Reserve 2.2 AWSH Motherwell * ARS Riverstone Bridge 3.4 ARS St Albans 3.0 AWS Uitenhage 0.2 Man Woodridge 0.2 Catchment  AWS Joubertina 0.4 Man Kareedouw 1.5 Man Kouga Dam 0.5 AWS Patensie 1.2 Man Swartkops  0.1 Man   Other Towns  AWS Addo NIL AWS Bisho/KWT NIL AWS Cape St Francis 2.6 AWS Cradock NIL AWS East London NIL AWS Fort Beaufort NIL AWS George 5.0 AWS Graaff Reinet NIL AWS Grahamstown NIL AWS Henry`s Flats NIL AWS Joubertina NIL AWS Mossel Bay 0.4 AWS Mthatha NIL AWS Plettenberg bay NIL AWS Port Alfred NIL AWS Queenstown NIL  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 